Draft the COA forms for NSF proposal with LLM. 

For USA NSF grant application, the Collaborators and Other Affiliations (COA) form is an Excel template requiring:
Part 1 - Professional Appointments (current and within last 5 years)
Institution
Start/end dates
Position title

Part 2 - Collaborators (past 48 months)
Co-authors
Co-editors
Research collaborators
Graduate/postdoc advisors
Graduate/postdoc advisees

LLM can used to generate a list of co-authors. For a free account of ChatGPT, these can be done by copy-paste the author names and affilation from the publications. 
The prompt can be "Extract names, affiliations from the following and put into a table. Put the names in the first column and affilation in second column". 
